    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-02-02T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-02-02T10:00:00-05:00" n="1101"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1101">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">304.1121 Young, James/13: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-02-03T00:00:00+09:00"
                            >February 3, 1940—midnight</date>.<lb/>[Received February 3—2:05
                        p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>82. Department’s 43, February 2, 3 p.m.<note n="54" xml:id="d1101fn54">Not
                        printed.</note>
                </p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>An attorney will not be permitted to visit Young until the termination of
                        the preliminary examination by the police which may continue for some time
                        longer and until the case is turned over to the judicial authorities.
                        Although an attorney could render no direct assistance at the present time,
                        the Embassy will immediately proceed to prepare a list of qualified
                        attorneys for the Department’s reference.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>On our own initiative and prior to the receipt of the Department’s
                        telegram the Embassy today made an informal request of the Foreign Office
                        for opportunity for a member of the staff to discuss the case with
                        Young.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
